    "biography": {
      "value": "<p>Chainwarden Militia are conscripts and press-ganged townsfolk given billhooks, mismatched shields, and just enough drill to hold a line. They fight not out of loyalty but obligation — debts, tithes, or the threat of the stockade keep them marching where the Wardens point. In open ground they are unremarkable, but packed shoulder-to-shoulder with other Chainwardens they become a wall of hooked blades that drags enemies into kill zones.</p>",
